description:
`AbisIp` table stores configuration parameters for A-bis IP interfaces in a radio access network, including timestamps, geographic location, cell and sector identifiers, various interface IDs, data format version, administrative state, retransmission parameters, IP addressing information, and Quality of Service (QoS) settings.

* `dateTime`: Timestamp of the record.
* `Area_Name`: Geographic area where the cell is located.
* `CellId`: Unique identifier for the cell site.
* `Id2`: Redundant cell identifier.
* `Id3`: Sector identifier.
* `Id4`: Auxiliary identifier (likely redundant).
* `vsDataType`: Data type indicator (specific to Ericsson).
* `vsDataFormatVersion`: Version of data format used.
* `AbisIp.userLabel`: User-defined label (currently empty).
* `AbisIp.gsmSectorName`: Name of the GSM sector.
* `AbisIp.initialRetransmissionPeriod`: Initial retransmission period.
* `AbisIp.administrativeState`: Administrative state of the interface.
* `AbisIp.retransmissionCap`: Retransmission capability.
* `AbisIp.abisIpId`:  Unique identifier for the A-bis IP interface.
* `AbisIp.ipv4Address`:  IPv4 address configuration string.
* `AbisIp.dscpSectorControlUL`: Differentiated Services Code Point (DSCP) for uplink sector control.
* `AbisIp.bscBrokerIpAddress`: IP address of the BSC broker.
* `AbisIp.maxRetransmission`: Maximum number of retransmissions.
* `AbisIp.keepAlivePeriod`: Keep-alive period.
